Subject:    Network naming draft RFC
From:       <a href="?a=95837784200005&r=1&w=2">Paul Mockapetris &lt;pvm () venera ! isi ! edu&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198903">1989-03-29 10:45:54</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626852&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626852&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Back about the time of the worm, there was a bunch of discussion on this
list about making network names available in the DNS.

At the last IETF meeting, several options were discussed, and the method
with the most support extended the notion to subnets.

The result is a draft RFC which describes the method, together with some
discussion about the alternatives, and some ideas for the future.  It is
available from Venera.ISI.EDU as ~ftp/pub/netname.doc.

Your comments are solicited.

paul

